FAQ

Frequently asked questions about life insurance

What type of insurance does Ladder offer?
View

Ladder offers flexible term life insurance. This is the simplest and typically most affordable type of life insurance. It provides a lump sum to your beneficiaries if you were to die during a certain period of time, known as the â€œterm.â€ Terms can be 10, 15, 20, 25, or 30 years, depending on your age.

What makes Ladder different?
View

With Ladder, you can do the entire application online and in many cases get an instant decision. Ladder also stands out for its flexibility. Youâ€™ll have the ability to adjust your coverage as your needs change. For example as your kids get older or your mortgage is paid off, you may need less coverage. 

Do I really need life insurance?
View

Most likely, yes. Itâ€™s not a topic most people are eager to think about. But if you have a partner, children, or parents who depend on you, life insurance provides a financial safety net if something unexpected happened to you. With life insurance, youâ€™d have the peace of mind of knowing that your mortgage and other bills would be taken care of if you were to pass away during the policy term. 

How long does it take to get a policy?
View

It depends, but Ladder makes the process as quick and easy as possible. The online application takes just a few minutes and some customers can get approved in about 5 minutes. In other cases, Ladder may need more time to review the application or get medical records.
